the first-place team.

00:04:48.121 --> 00:04:49.581 position:50% align:center
Wow. Interesting.

00:04:49.664 --> 00:04:50.915 position:50% align:center
Quite a point difference
between them

00:04:50.999 --> 00:04:52.167 position:50% align:center
and the next two schools.

00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:54.169 position:50% align:center
I wonder how this
will all play out.

00:04:54.252 --> 00:04:55.420 position:50% align:center
--Ms. Abe--
--Yes?

00:04:55.503 --> 00:04:57.380 position:50% align:center
With the only thing
left being free skate,

00:04:57.464 --> 00:04:58.923 position:50% align:center
I'm curious,
what would you predict

00:04:59.007 --> 00:05:00.383 position:50% align:center
will happen next?

00:05:00.467 --> 00:05:01.718 position:50% align:center
So hard to say!

00:05:01.801 --> 00:05:03.428 position:50% align:center
But while I fully expect
that all the schools

00:05:03.511 --> 00:05:05.597 position:50% align:center
will fight hard
until the bitter end,

00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:07.766 position:50% align:center
in this case, I think
it's pretty safe to say

00:05:07.849 --> 00:05:10.268 position:50% align:center
that St. Clavis Gakuin
and Ionodai High

00:05:10.352 --> 00:05:13.146 position:50% align:center
will be the top two finishers
of the fourth competition.

00:05:13.229 --> 00:05:14.564 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI]
Hey, Mr. Smug!

00:05:14.647 --> 00:05:15.899 position:50% align:center
Aren't you forgetting
to thank the person

00:05:15.982 --> 00:05:17.942 position:50% align:center
who carried your
butt home last night?

00:05:18.026 --> 00:05:19.861 position:50% align:center
My right knee will never
be the same, you know.

00:05:19.944 --> 00:05:21.696 position:50% align:center
[MAESHIMA]
Look, I'm sorry about that!

00:05:27.035 --> 00:05:30.080 position:50% align:center
[KUMADA] Izumi, FYI, the match
between your old teammates

00:05:30.163 --> 00:05:32.749 position:50% align:center
and Shinozaki's team
has already started.

00:05:32.832 --> 00:05:34.376 position:50% align:center
Feel free to go watch
it if you'd like.

00:05:34.459 --> 00:05:35.752 position:50% align:center
Thanks, but I'm good.

00:05:35.835 --> 00:05:37.170 position:50% align:center
I can watch the recording.

00:05:37.253 --> 00:05:38.797 position:50% align:center
Are you really this indifferent?

00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:40.924 position:50% align:center
[KUONJI]
Oh, Himekawa!

00:05:41.007 --> 00:05:44.344 position:50% align:center
Aw, there's no need to be
so cold, now, is there?

00:05:44.427 --> 00:05:47.555 position:50% align:center
Besides, it's very unattractive
to hide your emotions.

00:05:47.639 --> 00:05:49.057 position:50% align:center
Wouldn't you agree?

00:05:49.140 --> 00:05:50.266 position:50% align:center
[KOGAHARA SKATER A]
Number Two Prince?

00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:51.976 position:50% align:center
[KOGAHARA SKATER B]
Kuonji? From Yokohama?

00:05:52.060 --> 00:05:53.561 position:50% align:center
[KOGAHARA SKATER C]
He's really here?

00:05:53.645 --> 00:05:56.189 position:50% align:center
[KUONJI] I was in the area
on location for a TV show,

00:05:56.272 --> 00:05:57.982 position:50% align:center
so I thought I'd drop in.

00:05:58.066 --> 00:05:59.401 position:50% align:center
Did he make an appointment?

00:05:59.484 --> 00:06:00.902 position:50% align:center
Not that I know of, no.

00:06:00.985 --> 00:06:02.112 position:50% align:center
Come on, Himekawa.

00:06:02.195 --> 00:06:03.947 position:50% align:center
Let's go watch this match
between Maeshima

00:06:04.030 --> 00:06:06.324 position:50% align:center
and Shinozaki and decide
whether it's destiny

00:06:06.408 --> 00:06:08.076 position:50% align:center
or just another opening act.

00:06:08.159 --> 00:06:11.246 position:50% align:center
Let me take you to a nice
little Japanese cafe nearby.

00:06:11.329 --> 00:06:13.039 position:50% align:center
There's so much I want
to talk about with you.

00:06:13.123 --> 00:06:14.249 position:50% align:center
Wait, why on earth should I--

00:06:14.332 --> 00:06:15.750 position:50% align:center
Sounds like a good plan.

00:06:15.834 --> 00:06:17.127 position:50% align:center
You should go with him.

00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:18.586 position:50% align:center
You're far too tense
for your own good

00:06:18.670 --> 00:06:19.629 position:50% align:center
right now.

00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:21.006 position:50% align:center
Go and see if he
can teach you how

00:06:21.089 --> 00:06:22.632 position:50% align:center
to unwind and relax a little.

00:06:22.716 --> 00:06:23.842 position:50% align:center
You can't be serious!

00:06:23.925 --> 00:06:26.052 position:50% align:center
This Yokohama guy?
I refuse to acce--

00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:27.554 position:50% align:center
[KUMADA] If you ditch and
go home instead,

00:06:27.637 --> 00:06:29.931 position:50% align:center
I'll take you off
the starting roster.

00:06:30.015 --> 00:06:31.599 position:50% align:center
It looks like you've
got permission.

00:06:31.683 --> 00:06:33.852 position:50% align:center
Come on, let's go,
"Princess River."

00:06:33.935 --> 00:06:35.437 position:50% align:center
Don't ever call me that.

00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:37.063 position:50% align:center
[CROWD chattering]

00:06:43.528 --> 00:06:44.904 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B] It looks like
they've begun smoothing

00:06:44.988 --> 00:06:48.867 position:50% align:center
the ice back down for
the upcoming free skate.

00:06:48.950 --> 00:06:50.076 position:50% align:center
So, while we have a moment,

00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:52.162 position:50% align:center
let's look back at
St. Clavis Gakuin

00:06:52.245 --> 00:06:54.706 position:50% align:center
and Ionodai High's
short programs.

00:06:54.789 --> 00:06:56.332 position:50% align:center
First, what's your
general impression

00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:58.418 position:50% align:center
of the two schools, Ms. Abe?

00:06:58.501 --> 00:07:01.129 position:50% align:center
[COMMENTATOR B] Well, I'm sure
St. Clavis needs no explanation.

00:07:01.212 --> 00:07:02.964 position:50% align:center
They've been called an
unbeatable powerhouse,

00:07:03.048 --> 00:07:06.343 position:50% align:center
and true to form, they've
been steady and reliable.

00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:08.470 position:50% align:center
Shinozaki's teamwork
is better than expected,

00:07:08.553 --> 00:07:10.472 position:50% align:center
given his history
competing in singles,

00:07:10.555 --> 00:07:13.933 position:50% align:center
so their line-up is full of
strong skaters this year.

00:07:14.017 --> 00:07:15.477 position:50% align:center
They're one or two
rungs above the schools

00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:18.688 position:50% align:center
they're competing against,
and that's all there is to it.

00:07:18.772 --> 00:07:20.690 position:50% align:center
But just like in their
previous competition,

00:07:20.774 --> 00:07:22.567 position:50% align:center
the entertainment aspect
seems difficult

00:07:22.650 --> 00:07:24.527 position:50% align:center
for Shinozaki, so they
didn't gain as many

00:07:24.611 --> 00:07:26.154 position:50% align:center
points as expected.

00:07:26.237 --> 00:07:29.240 position:50% align:center
True, but it's still a pretty
high score, regardless.

00:07:29.324 --> 00:07:31.451 position:50% align:center
What about Ionodai High School?

00:07:31.534 --> 00:07:32.744 position:50% align:center
[COMMENTATOR B]
Compared to their performance

00:07:32.827 --> 00:07:33.912 position:50% align:center
in the first competition,

00:07:33.995 --> 00:07:35.997 position:50% align:center
they feel a little surer
and more stable.

00:07:36.081 --> 00:07:37.374 position:50% align:center
They've added this
wild edginess...

00:07:37.457 --> 00:07:39.000 position:50% align:center
Hey, why're you streaming this?

00:07:39.084 --> 00:07:41.586 position:50% align:center
Watch the live broadcast
on the TV in the lobby.

00:07:41.670 --> 00:07:43.880 position:50% align:center
Not in here.

00:07:43.963 --> 00:07:45.840 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] I don't want to
go out there, do you?

00:07:45.924 --> 00:07:47.842 position:50% align:center
No, who wants to
watch the others?

00:07:47.926 --> 00:07:49.302 position:50% align:center
[BOTH laugh]

00:07:49.386 --> 00:07:51.096 position:50% align:center
Right! Exactly my point.

00:07:51.179 --> 00:07:52.347 position:50% align:center
Maybe just the best teams.

00:07:52.430 --> 00:07:53.682 position:50% align:center
Very well.

00:07:53.765 --> 00:07:56.309 position:50% align:center
I'll let you know when the
top-ranking teams skate.

00:07:56.393 --> 00:07:57.727 position:50% align:center
He could tell what
they were saying?

00:07:57.811 --> 00:07:59.354 position:50% align:center
Well, he is their father.

00:08:05.360 --> 00:08:06.820 position:50% align:center
Pretty good pics, right?

00:08:06.903 --> 00:08:08.196 position:50% align:center
Yeah, they are.

00:08:08.279 --> 00:08:10.365 position:50% align:center
Keep it up, and tell the
others to do the same thing.

00:08:10.448 --> 00:08:11.449 position:50% align:center
You got it.

00:08:11.533 --> 00:08:13.326 position:50% align:center
You should go eat now,
while you can.

00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:15.870 position:50% align:center
The free skate is quite a bit
longer than the short program.

00:08:15.954 --> 00:08:16.955 position:50% align:center
Good call.

00:08:18.081 --> 00:08:20.834 position:50% align:center
Second. Not a bad start at all.

00:08:22.752 --> 00:08:24.421 position:50% align:center
[TERAUCHI] Right now,
the three teams going first

00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:27.257 position:50% align:center
are in the bottom rink for
their six-minute practice.

00:08:27.340 --> 00:08:29.175 position:50% align:center
Ours will start
after that, but...

00:08:29.259 --> 00:08:30.135 position:50% align:center
Wait.

00:08:30.218 --> 00:08:31.970 position:50% align:center
Where'd Maeshima run off to?

00:08:32.053 --> 00:08:32.846 position:50% align:center
Who knows?

00:08:32.929 --> 00:08:34.264 position:50% align:center
[YUKIMITSU]
You idiot!

00:08:34.347 --> 00:08:36.099 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI] He was dancing
around the basement levels,

00:08:36.182 --> 00:08:37.475 position:50% align:center
so I brought him back up.

00:08:37.559 --> 00:08:39.060 position:50% align:center
Look how you trashed
your costume!

00:08:39.144 --> 00:08:41.312 position:50% align:center
Hurry and take it off,
then sit down!

00:08:41.396 --> 00:08:43.148 position:50% align:center
What's going on? Wow.

00:08:43.231 --> 00:08:44.357 position:50% align:center
Doesn't sound good.

00:08:44.441 --> 00:08:46.484 position:50% align:center
--Tomo, come help me!
--[KUBOTA] Right!

00:08:46.568 --> 00:08:48.278 position:50% align:center
What in the world
were you thinking?

00:08:48.361 --> 00:08:50.655 position:50% align:center
Wearing yourself out
before you go on.

00:08:50.739 --> 00:08:52.824 position:50% align:center
We've got barely any time left!

00:08:52.907 --> 00:08:54.325 position:50% align:center
[MAESHIMA]
I'm resting now, jeez.

00:08:54.409 --> 00:08:55.201 position:50% align:center
Get the hair dryer.

00:08:55.285 --> 00:08:56.619 position:50% align:center
Yep, on it.

00:08:56.703 --> 00:08:58.329 position:50% align:center
Do you feel any remorse at all
for what you've done?

00:08:58.413 --> 00:08:59.539 position:50% align:center
Calm down.

00:09:00.331 --> 00:09:02.667 position:50% align:center
Maeshima, what were you doing?

00:09:02.751 --> 00:09:04.002 position:50% align:center
I was practicing.

00:09:04.085 --> 00:09:06.379 position:50% align:center
You have to be careful.
Don't overdo it like that.

00:09:06.463 --> 00:09:08.465 position:50% align:center
I know, and I'm sorry.

00:09:08.548 --> 00:09:10.091 position:50% align:center
Although, you're not
a serious skater

00:09:10.175 --> 00:09:12.302 position:50% align:center
if you don't give it your all.

00:09:12.385 --> 00:09:14.095 position:50% align:center
I just want to push
myself as close

00:09:14.179 --> 00:09:17.265 position:50% align:center
to my limit as I can,
'cause I had that break.

00:09:17.349 --> 00:09:19.184 position:50% align:center
But I'm sorry for
causing Yuki trouble.

00:09:19.267 --> 00:09:20.727 position:50% align:center
[YUKIMITSU]
It's fine, just be quiet.

00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:23.563 position:50% align:center
Our strategy is what I told
you in the meeting yesterday.

00:09:23.646 --> 00:09:24.939 position:50% align:center
You all remember
the changes we made

00:09:25.023 --> 00:09:27.192 position:50% align:center
--to the routine, right?
--[TERAUCHI] Yes, sir.

00:09:27.275 --> 00:09:29.527 position:50% align:center
That's the untamed horse
everyone's talking about.

00:09:29.611 --> 00:09:31.321 position:50% align:center
The rumors are right,
throwing his team

00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:33.531 position:50% align:center
into chaos right before a skate.

00:09:33.615 --> 00:09:34.741 position:50% align:center
What's it matter?

00:09:34.824 --> 00:09:36.034 position:50% align:center
I mean, everyone
has their own way

00:09:36.117 --> 00:09:38.411 position:50% align:center
of getting and
staying motivated.

00:09:38.495 --> 00:09:39.829 position:50% align:center
Plus, the way you're talking,

00:09:39.913 --> 00:09:41.539 position:50% align:center
it could end up leading
you to underestimate

00:09:41.623 --> 00:09:43.083 position:50% align:center
your opponent.

00:09:43.166 --> 00:09:45.168 position:50% align:center
Don't be distracted by others.

00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:46.419 position:50% align:center
[YAMASHITA, MICHINAGA]
Yes, sir!

