to reward passion like that.

00:12:42.053 --> 00:12:44.347 position:50% align:center
It can be easy to cross
the line, though.

00:12:44.431 --> 00:12:45.890 position:50% align:center
If he doesn't learn
how to control himself

00:12:45.974 --> 00:12:47.809 position:50% align:center
and his feelings, fast,

00:12:47.892 --> 00:12:50.061 position:50% align:center
it'll end up like
the first competition:

00:12:50.145 --> 00:12:52.022 position:50% align:center
They'll fall. Just watch.

00:12:56.276 --> 00:12:57.902 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI]
Emotional control?

00:12:57.986 --> 00:12:59.487 position:50% align:center
What's that?

00:12:59.571 --> 00:13:01.531 position:50% align:center
The guy's not a
very good student.

00:13:03.491 --> 00:13:05.827 position:50% align:center
I know I'm not
really one to talk,

00:13:05.910 --> 00:13:08.246 position:50% align:center
but Maeshima's working hard
'cause he wants to win.

00:13:08.329 --> 00:13:10.749 position:50% align:center
Understand that much.

00:13:10.832 --> 00:13:12.167 position:50% align:center
You should be
encouraging him to skate

00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:13.501 position:50% align:center
with everything he's got,

00:13:13.585 --> 00:13:16.254 position:50% align:center
not asking him to make
himself smaller for you.

00:13:16.338 --> 00:13:18.298 position:50% align:center
Yeah.
We're gonna back him up.

00:13:18.381 --> 00:13:20.425 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI]
No, don't do that.

00:13:20.508 --> 00:13:23.053 position:50% align:center
If you think of it that way,
you'll make yourself small.

00:13:23.136 --> 00:13:25.263 position:50% align:center
You should rise up to meet him.

00:13:25.347 --> 00:13:27.432 position:50% align:center
You came to make Himuro
taste bitter defeat,

00:13:27.515 --> 00:13:28.475 position:50% align:center
isn't that right?

00:13:28.558 --> 00:13:30.101 position:50% align:center
This is your chance, guys.

00:13:33.396 --> 00:13:35.732 position:50% align:center
Fine, I guess we'll at least
hear you out on this.

00:13:35.815 --> 00:13:37.692 position:50% align:center
Every member of this
team should already have

00:13:37.776 --> 00:13:40.028 position:50% align:center
the necessary technique
to keep up with him.

00:13:40.111 --> 00:13:41.363 position:50% align:center
Don't you agree, Coach?

00:13:43.073 --> 00:13:44.824 position:50% align:center
Well, yeah. I taught you that.

00:13:44.908 --> 00:13:46.618 position:50% align:center
Whatever.

00:13:46.701 --> 00:13:48.661 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI]
Please. Vice Captain.

00:13:48.745 --> 00:13:50.997 position:50% align:center
If you can stick with
Maeshima and let him lead,

00:13:51.081 --> 00:13:52.332 position:50% align:center
the whole performance
will improve,

00:13:52.415 --> 00:13:54.250 position:50% align:center
and it'll stand out
to the judges.

00:13:54.334 --> 00:13:56.419 position:50% align:center
Also gives the wing
and guards more room.

00:13:56.503 --> 00:13:57.879 position:50% align:center
Easier said than done.

00:13:57.962 --> 00:13:59.214 position:50% align:center
I believe in you.

00:13:59.297 --> 00:14:01.007 position:50% align:center
Except you totally don't.

00:14:01.091 --> 00:14:02.384 position:50% align:center
Hey, now, have
I ever lied to you

00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:03.718 position:50% align:center
at a time like this?

00:14:05.428 --> 00:14:06.388 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI]
Jonouchi!

00:14:06.471 --> 00:14:07.555 position:50% align:center
[JONOUCHI yelps]

00:14:07.639 --> 00:14:09.391 position:50% align:center
D'jyou lose some sleep
gaming last night?

00:14:09.474 --> 00:14:10.850 position:50% align:center
[JONOUCHI]
No way, I swear!

00:14:10.934 --> 00:14:12.811 position:50% align:center
I could tell in the
short program.

00:14:12.894 --> 00:14:13.978 position:50% align:center
Don't sweat it, though.

00:14:14.062 --> 00:14:15.522 position:50% align:center
They say being a little
tired can actually

00:14:15.605 --> 00:14:17.899 position:50% align:center
enhance your
performance at times.

00:14:17.982 --> 00:14:19.109 position:50% align:center
[JONOUCHI]
Really?

00:14:19.192 --> 00:14:21.528 position:50% align:center
It'd be cool to say
"I removed my limiter,"

00:14:21.611 --> 00:14:22.779 position:50% align:center
wouldn't you agree?

00:14:25.907 --> 00:14:26.825 position:50% align:center
Heck yeah!

00:14:26.908 --> 00:14:28.326 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI]
Pulled it outta my butt.

00:14:30.662 --> 00:14:32.247 position:50% align:center
What's wrong?

00:14:32.330 --> 00:14:33.331 position:50% align:center
Do your best.

00:14:33.415 --> 00:14:34.874 position:50% align:center
[AKIMITSU]
At what?

00:14:34.958 --> 00:14:36.126 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI]
Go.

00:14:36.209 --> 00:14:38.253 position:50% align:center
Seize the victory with
everything you've got.

00:14:38.336 --> 00:14:41.006 position:50% align:center
That's what this
team's all about!

00:14:41.089 --> 00:14:42.340 position:50% align:center
[MAESHIMA]
I'm gonna win!

00:14:42.424 --> 00:14:44.092 position:50% align:center
--[TERAUCHI] I'm gonna win!
--[KIRIYAMA] Win it.

00:14:44.175 --> 00:14:45.969 position:50% align:center
[JONOUCHI]
I'm so freakin' cool!

00:14:49.389 --> 00:14:52.684 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B] They did it!
All five landed it cleanly!

00:14:52.767 --> 00:14:55.020 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow, my first
time seeing this.

00:14:55.103 --> 00:14:56.354 position:50% align:center
Yeah, mine too.

00:14:56.438 --> 00:14:58.189 position:50% align:center
It's like they're shouting
with their whole bodies.

00:14:58.273 --> 00:15:00.191 position:50% align:center
Sho and the others are so cool!

00:15:00.275 --> 00:15:02.110 position:50% align:center
[AKIMITSU] Stop getting all
excited, you guys,

00:15:02.193 --> 00:15:03.528 position:50% align:center
it doesn't help.

00:15:03.611 --> 00:15:07.032 position:50% align:center
I mean, if you do that,
then I'll just want to win, too!

00:15:07.115 --> 00:15:08.783 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B] Skate-leading
performances are sometimes

00:15:08.867 --> 00:15:11.411 position:50% align:center
called "group dancing,"
but I've never seen a routine

00:15:11.494 --> 00:15:13.830 position:50% align:center
fit that description
quite like this!

00:15:19.044 --> 00:15:20.670 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:15:20.754 --> 00:15:21.755 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B]
They did it!

00:15:21.838 --> 00:15:23.089 position:50% align:center
They really did it!

00:15:23.173 --> 00:15:24.841 position:50% align:center
Ionodai High did not
let the results

00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:26.843 position:50% align:center
of the first competition
haunt them.

00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:28.345 position:50% align:center
They gave a
breathtaking performance

00:15:28.428 --> 00:15:30.472 position:50% align:center
that proved how
amazing they are!

00:15:41.649 --> 00:15:42.650 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B]
There it is!

00:15:42.734 --> 00:15:45.403 position:50% align:center
With a total score of 138.48,

00:15:45.487 --> 00:15:48.073 position:50% align:center
they've got the highest
scores in this competition!

00:15:48.156 --> 00:15:50.408 position:50% align:center
They've shot themselves
straight up to the top!

00:15:50.492 --> 00:15:52.494 position:50% align:center
[COMMENTATOR B] That's because
they didn't make any mistakes,

00:15:52.577 --> 00:15:54.329 position:50% align:center
each skater earned
every point he could,

00:15:54.412 --> 00:15:56.456 position:50% align:center
and they really leaned
into the artistry!

00:15:56.539 --> 00:15:58.583 position:50% align:center
I think even St. Clavis
will have a hard time

00:15:58.667 --> 00:15:59.876 position:50% align:center
beating this score.

00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:02.671 position:50% align:center
Shinozaki!
Well, did you see us skate?

00:16:02.754 --> 00:16:04.756 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]
This thing is totally ours.

00:16:04.839 --> 00:16:06.591 position:50% align:center
You haven't changed at all.

00:16:06.675 --> 00:16:09.511 position:50% align:center
I'll tell you one more time.

00:16:09.594 --> 00:16:11.471 position:50% align:center
You will never be
able to beat me,

00:16:11.554 --> 00:16:13.640 position:50% align:center
no matter how much you
think you've progressed.

00:16:13.723 --> 00:16:16.935 position:50% align:center
In fact, you're
actually regressing.

00:16:17.018 --> 00:16:18.269 position:50% align:center
Hey, what are you doing?

00:16:18.353 --> 00:16:19.688 position:50% align:center
Stop, Maeshima!

00:16:19.771 --> 00:16:21.314 position:50% align:center
You're a little jerk.

00:16:21.398 --> 00:16:23.608 position:50% align:center
Looking down on me, always!

00:16:23.692 --> 00:16:24.651 position:50% align:center
Careful.

00:16:24.734 --> 00:16:26.486 position:50% align:center
We may feel the
need to report you.

00:16:26.569 --> 00:16:29.656 position:50% align:center
Sorry about this, for real.
Apologize.

00:16:29.739 --> 00:16:31.658 position:50% align:center
[SASUGAI] There's no
need for that, is there?

00:16:31.741 --> 00:16:34.035 position:50% align:center
You insulted us first,
don't forget.

00:16:34.119 --> 00:16:36.371 position:50% align:center
Besides, if we were
to get suspended,

00:16:36.454 --> 00:16:39.040 position:50% align:center
you'd be pretty disappointed,
too, wouldn't you?

00:16:39.124 --> 00:16:40.709 position:50% align:center
Mr. Shinozaki.

00:16:43.003 --> 00:16:44.212 position:50% align:center
Oh, no, don't worry.

00:16:44.295 --> 00:16:45.714 position:50% align:center
We're happy to
compete against you

00:16:45.797 --> 00:16:47.132 position:50% align:center
fair and square.

00:16:55.056 --> 00:16:57.559 position:50% align:center
Captain, we're still going
with the plan, right?

00:16:57.642 --> 00:16:59.894 position:50% align:center
That's right.
I'm counting on you two.

00:16:59.978 --> 00:17:01.479 position:50% align:center
You bet. Let's do it.

00:17:05.108 --> 00:17:06.401 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B] It's time
for the final performance

00:17:06.484 --> 00:17:09.029 position:50% align:center
of the fourth competition
in this series.

00:17:09.112 --> 00:17:10.488 position:50% align:center
Which means we
can stop wondering

00:17:10.572 --> 00:17:13.283 position:50% align:center
what the favorite to win
will show us today!

00:17:13.366 --> 00:17:14.784 position:50% align:center
[music playing]

00:17:22.125 --> 00:17:23.835 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:17:23.918 --> 00:17:25.003 position:50% align:center
The music is different,

00:17:25.086 --> 00:17:27.672 position:50% align:center
but it's the same
choreography as Ionodai!

00:17:27.756 --> 00:17:29.257 position:50% align:center
[COMMENTATOR B]
Shinozaki is their only lead,

00:17:29.341 --> 00:17:31.968 position:50% align:center
but they've obviously changed
up their entire routine!

00:17:35.555 --> 00:17:36.848 position:50% align:center
Is this a coincidence?

00:17:36.931 --> 00:17:38.183 position:50% align:center
Of course it isn't.

00:17:38.266 --> 00:17:41.019 position:50% align:center
To be able to change
this much last minute.

00:17:41.102 --> 00:17:42.687 position:50% align:center
[COMMENTATOR B]
In contrast to Ionodai,

00:17:42.771 --> 00:17:44.481 position:50% align:center
who used their
passion and power,

00:17:44.564 --> 00:17:46.524 position:50% align:center
St. Clavis's performance
is so fluid!

00:17:46.608 --> 00:17:48.026 position:50% align:center
[ANNOUNCER B] Looks like
they've gone back to their

00:17:48.109 --> 00:17:49.486 position:50% align:center
original routine.

00:17:49.569 --> 00:17:51.363 position:50% align:center
[HIMURO]
That Shinozaki may be quiet,

00:17:51.446 --> 00:17:54.824 position:50% align:center
but it's becoming clear
he's fiercely competitive.

00:17:54.908 --> 00:17:57.494 position:50% align:center
[YAMASHITA] Wait, we're
changing the routine?

00:17:57.577 --> 00:18:00.747 position:50% align:center
Just the opening.
We'll do what Ionodai did.

00:18:00.830 --> 00:18:02.624 position:50% align:center
But why do you wanna do that?

00:18:02.707 --> 00:18:04.167 position:50% align:center
What, did they set you off?

00:18:06.419 --> 00:18:07.879 position:50% align:center
You're good enough
to handle this.

00:18:07.962 --> 00:18:09.547 position:50% align:center
Like all of us are.

00:18:09.631 --> 00:18:10.924 position:50% align:center
One of our later
elements will come

00:18:11.007 --> 00:18:12.217 position:50% align:center
at the beginning now,

00:18:12.300 --> 00:18:14.135 position:50% align:center
so we'll make that
adjustment, too.

00:18:14.219 --> 00:18:16.971 position:50% align:center
[MICHINAGA] I mean,
we probably can, but still.

00:18:17.055 --> 00:18:18.723 position:50% align:center
I'm down. Let's do it.

00:18:18.807 --> 00:18:19.724 position:50% align:center
Captain?

00:18:19.808 --> 00:18:20.892 position:50% align:center
I think it's smart.

00:18:20.975 --> 00:18:22.560 position:50% align:center
You saw how they skated today.

00:18:22.644 --> 00:18:24.020 position:50% align:center
If they keep that up,
we can expect them

00:18:24.104 --> 00:18:26.773 position:50% align:center
to continue getting high scores.

00:18:26.856 --> 00:18:28.024 position:50% align:center
Left alone,
they might become more

00:18:28.108 --> 00:18:30.068 position:50% align:center
of a nuisance than we'd like.

00:18:30.151 --> 00:18:33.154 position:50% align:center
That's why, now,
we've got to crush them.

00:18:33.238 --> 00:18:36.366 position:50% align:center
We'll make sure they know
who the champions are.

00:18:36.449 --> 00:18:38.243 position:50% align:center
That sound good, Shinozaki?

00:18:41.371 --> 00:18:44.082 position:50% align:center
I was surprised at first
when he suggested it,

00:18:44.165 --> 00:18:45.959 position:50% align:center
but it shows how
conscious Shinozaki is

00:18:46.042 --> 00:18:47.669 position:50% align:center
of Maeshima's power.

00:18:47.752 --> 00:18:48.628 position:50% align:center
[YAMASHITA]
It's true.

00:18:48.712 --> 00:18:50.797 position:50% align:center
Ionodai really did perform well.

00:18:50.880 --> 00:18:52.716 position:50% align:center
[MICHINAGA]
But we can't lose this.

00:18:52.799 --> 00:18:54.801 position:50% align:center
[KURAYOSHI] Our goal is
to win twice in a row.

00:18:54.884 --> 00:18:56.720 position:50% align:center
To not let anyone
else take the top.

00:18:56.803 --> 00:18:58.304 position:50% align:center
A complete victory!

00:18:58.388 --> 00:19:00.181 position:50% align:center
